HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 82
By Garrett
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Don Dallenbach of
Hendersonville.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body were greatly saddened to learn of the
passing of Don Dallenbach of Hendersonville; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dallenbach was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional, who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in Taipei, Taiwan, on September 9, 1966, Mr. Dallenbach was the son
of Don and Laurie Dallenbach and a 1984 graduate of Hendersonville High School; and
WHEREAS, he devoted his professional years to serving as a firefighter with the
Hendersonville Fire Department for thirty-two years; as a captain on C Shift at Station 5, he was
admired for his courage and commitment to his community, and his legacy as a firefighter will
continue to inspire future generations of firefighters who follow in his footsteps; and
WHEREAS, Don Dallenbach was deeply devoted to his family, and he always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dallenbach enjoyed the loving companionship of his wife, Denise
Dallenbach, for twenty-eight years, and was the proud father of two sons, Dylan (Sierah)
Dallenbach and Drew (Emily) Dallenbach; and
WHEREAS, Don Dallenbach is further survived by his mother-in-law, Patsy Osgatharp,
and father-in-law, Jack Osgatharp; his siblings, Heath (Emily) Hagan, Jeanie (Eric) Bandy, and
Casey (Lauren) Hagan; his cousin who was like a sister to him, Shannon Dallenbach
Thompson; his aunt, Sue Tricario; a host of aunts, uncles, cousins, and friends; and the
cherished members of his Hendersonville Fire Department family; and
